            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-358] Throw exception when ledger does not exist</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-358</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, openLedger() in the BookKeeper client returns null if the ledger ID does not exist on ZK. Maybe it would be better to throw a specific exception so it can be handled by the client side. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
